OL,3,C20,000 renters will be 'pulled into
OL,4,Cpoverty' over housing allowance freeze
OL,6,FRachelle Earwaker, senior economist at
OL,7,Fthe Joseph Rowntree Foundation said:
OL,8,F"Instead of not knowing whether
OL,9,Fthey'll be able to pay their rent
OL,10,Fbecause the support they get has been
OL,11,Ffrozen, private renters need to know
OL,12,Fthat LHA will rise in line with local
OL,13,Frents each year.
OL,15,F"The Budget presents a clear
OL,16,Fopportunity for the government to act
OL,17,Fnow by permanently linking LHA to
OL,18,Flocal rents to prevent this and show
OL,19,Ftheir commitment to improving the
OL,20,Flives of some of Britain's poorest
OL,21,Fprivate renters."
